  "text": "It has been known that the FC-rank of a regular linear ordering, even automatic linear ordering is finite, cf. [CITATION_1] . In this note we established the result that the FC-rank of a context-free linear ordering is less than ω ω . Our proof method relying on the corresponding result for scattered context-free linear orderings in [CITATION_2] was the expected one with key ingredient being that the FC-rank of every closed scattered interval in the lexicographic ordering of a context-free prefix language L is bounded by ω n , where n is a constant depending only on the grammar (in weak GNF) generating L.",
